SUMMARY:

This software is licensed under the MIT License with the Commons Clause.

What you CAN do:
✅ Use the software for personal use
✅ Use the software for commercial use (internally)
✅ Modify the source code
✅ Distribute the software
✅ Use it in your company/organization
✅ Create derivative works
✅ Use it for educational purposes
✅ Contribute to the project

What you CANNOT do:
❌ Sell the software itself
❌ Sell hosted services based primarily on this software
❌ Sell support/consulting services where the primary value is this software
❌ Charge fees for providing this software as a service

Examples:

ALLOWED:
- Using PhotoManager Pro to organize your personal photo collection
- Using PhotoManager Pro in your company to manage internal photo archives
- Modifying PhotoManager Pro and sharing your modifications for free
- Including PhotoManager Pro in a larger product that provides substantial additional value
- Teaching photography courses and recommending PhotoManager Pro to students

NOT ALLOWED:
- Selling PhotoManager Pro as a standalone product
- Creating a paid web service that just runs PhotoManager Pro
- Charging money for hosting PhotoManager Pro for others
- Selling PhotoManager Pro support as your primary business offering

If you have questions about what you can or cannot do, please open an issue on GitHub.
